  "text": "The core document model architecture in LibreOffice is defined across five key C++ header files:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx, line 182): The base document shell class that all document types inherit from. Defined as `class SFX2_DLLPUBLIC SfxObjectShell : public SfxShell, public SotObject, public ::comphelper::IEmbeddedHelper`. This is the foundational framework for all document objects in LibreOffice.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx, line 196): The Writer (word processor) document class. Defined as `class SwDoc final`. This represents the model of a Writer document and is the core data structure for all word processing documents.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class. Defined as `class ScDocument`. This is the main document class for all spreadsheet data and operations in Calc.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338): The Impress/Draw document class. Defined as `class SD_DLLPUBLIC SdDrawDocument final : public FmFormModel`. This is the document model for presentation and drawing documents.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103): The LibreOffice application framework entry point. Defined as `class SFX2_DLLPUBLIC SfxApplication final : public SfxShell`. This is a singleton class that serves as the main application instance and framework for LibreOffice.\n\nThese files form the architectural backbone of LibreOffice's document model system, with SfxObjectShell serving as the universal base class and SfxApplication providing the application-level framework."
}

